  "texts": [
    "We plot the RL model's predictions as inputs become more unfamiliar in Fig. 3.",
    "Similarly to the previous SFT experiments, the RL models predict higher likelihoods for the ground truth answer when faced with familiar inputs.",
    "As inputs become more unfamiliar, we see that models trained with the two different reward functions exhibit different behavior.",
    "While models with the first reward function increasingly produced random guesses, models with the second reward function increasingly produced abstaining answers.",
    "These results show that models finetuned with an RL loss also default towards P unf (y) as inputs become more unfamiliar."
  ],
